## Rules

### 1. Default exports for components

```js
// ✅ Default export for the main component
export default function ProductCard({ ... }) { ... }

// ✅ Named exports only for sub-components or utilities within the same file
export function ProductCardSkeleton() { ... }
```

### 2. Destructure props in the function signature

```jsx
// ✅
export default function Button({ children, variant = 'primary', disabled = false, className, onClick }) {

// ❌
export default function Button(props) {
  const { children, variant } = props
```

### 3. Always accept and forward `className`

Every reusable component in `components/ui/` must accept a `className` prop and apply it last via `cn()`.

### 4. Feature components receive data as props — never fetch internally

```jsx
// ✅ Feature component — receives data from page
export default function ProductGrid({ products }) {
  return (
    <section>
      {products.map((p) => <ProductCard key={p.id} {...p} />)}
    </section>
  )
}

// ❌ Feature component fetching its own data
export default function ProductGrid() {
  const [products, setProducts] = useState([])
  useEffect(() => { fetch('/api/products')... }, [])
}
```

### 5. Page components are async Server Components

```jsx
// app/(marketing)/products/page.jsx
export default async function ProductsPage() {
  const products = await getProducts(); // async server fetch
  return <ProductGrid products={products} />;
}
```

### 6. One component per file

Never define two exported components in the same file unless they are tightly coupled sub-components (e.g., `Tab` and `TabPanel`).

### 7. Keys on lists

Always use a stable, unique `id` or `slug` as the key — never use array index.

```jsx
// ✅
{
  products.map((p) => <ProductCard key={p.id} {...p} />);
}
{
  products.map((p) => <ProductCard key={p.slug} {...p} />);
}

// ❌
{
  products.map((p, i) => <ProductCard key={i} {...p} />);
}
```

